<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Iran, Golestan Province, Shirinabad village, unnamed river; 
<geoCoordinate degrees="36" direction="north" minutes="48" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="01.44" value="36.8004">36°48'01.44&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
/ 
<geoCoordinate degrees="55" direction="east" minutes="01" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="05.78" value="55.018272">55°01'05.78&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
(locality no. 108); 740 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Northern Iran. Known only from three sites in the eastern Alborz (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471965" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae inhabit streams at middle altitude, 740-1450 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471965" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="main morphological diagnostics of larvae">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Main morphological diagnostics of larvae.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(i) abdominal terga V-VII with triangular or T-shaped medial macula (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="F43" captionText="Figure 43. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F-H middle leg in dorsal view I-K abdominal terga L abdominal sterna II-VI M gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471966" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">43I-K</figureCitation>
); (ii) abdominal sterna without coloration pattern (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="F43" captionText="Figure 43. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F-H middle leg in dorsal view I-K abdominal terga L abdominal sterna II-VI M gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471966" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">43B, L</figureCitation>
); (iii) tergum X without postero-lateral projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figure 44. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view K sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure44" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471967" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">44J</figureCitation>
); (iv) femora with medial hypodermal spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="F43" captionText="Figure 43. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F-H middle leg in dorsal view I-K abdominal terga L abdominal sterna II-VI M gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471966" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">43F-H</figureCitation>
); (v) gill plates VII (in natural position from ventral view) wide (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="F43" captionText="Figure 43. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F-H middle leg in dorsal view I-K abdominal terga L abdominal sterna II-VI M gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471966" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">43M</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figure 44. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view K sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure44" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471967" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">44H, I</figureCitation>
); (vi) setae on abdominal terga hair-like (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figure 44. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view K sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure44" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471967" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">44E</figureCitation>
); (vii) gill plates III with well-developed projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 44" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figure 44. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view K sternum IX of female with observed variability." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure44" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471967" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">44G</figureCitation>
); (viii) shape of head of male oval trapezoidal (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 43" captionStartId="F43" captionText="Figure 43. Epeorus (Caucasiron) shargi, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F-H middle leg in dorsal view I-K abdominal terga L abdominal sterna II-VI M gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure43" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471966" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">43D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Taxonomy</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species was described based on larvae collected from Alborz Mts. (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" author="Hrivniak, Ľ" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="71 - 102" refId="B21" refString="Hrivniak, Ľ, Sroka, P, Bojkova, J, Godunko, RJ, Imanpour Namin, J, Bagheri, S, Nejat, F, Abdoli, A, Staniczek, AH, 2020a. Diversity and distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in Iran, with descriptions of three new species. ZooKeys 947: 71 - 102, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" title="Diversity and distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) in Iran, with descriptions of three new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.947.51259" volume="947" year="2020 a">Hrivniak et al. 2020a</bibRefCitation>
). Imagines not described. The type series is currently deposited in SMNS, IECA, and MMTT_DOE.
</paragraph>
